{"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"name":"python3","display_name":"Python 3","language":"python"},"language_info":{"name":"python","version":"3.12.13","mimetype":"text/x-python","codemirror_mode":{"name":"ipython","version":3},"pygments_lexer":"ipython3","nbconvert_exporter":"python","file_extension":".py"},"colab":{"provenance":[]}},"nbformat_minor":5,"nbformat":4,"cells":[{"id":"f0ee0d70","cell_type":"code","source":"#Basic imports\nimport numpy as np\nimport pandas as pd\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\nimport seaborn as sns\nimport joblib","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-07-09T16:08:33.097989Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-07-09T16:08:33.098251Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-07-09T16:08:35.553073Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-07-09T16:08:33.098229Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-07-09T16:08:35.552283Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":1},{"id":"c2f92c11","cell_type":"markdown","source":"# ✈️ Airline Customer Churn Prediction: Model Development and Deployment (v2)\n\n**What changed from v1, and why:**\n\n1. **Ranking metric: ROC-AUC → PR-AUC (average precision).** With a ~14.5:1 imbalance, ROC-AUC is dominated by how well a model ranks the huge majority class, so it can look strong even when it barely finds positives. PR-AUC (average precision) is the standard metric for rare-event problems and is not fooled this way. All five Optuna objectives below now optimize `scoring=\"average_precision\"` instead of `\"roc_auc\"`.\n2. **Model selection now flips.** Under ROC-AUC, plain unweighted Random Forest edged out the two imbalance-aware models (XGBoost with tuned `scale_pos_weight`, BalancedRandomForestClassifier) even though those were built specifically to handle the imbalance. Under PR-AUC, **BalancedRandomForestClassifier wins**, as expected.\n3. **Threshold tuning now compares two business framings, not just F1.** F1 weights precision and recall equally, which is the wrong assumption for a retention product: missing a churner (false negative) is usually far costlier than an unnecessary retention offer (false positive). We now compute both a pure **F1-optimal** threshold and a **recall-floor** threshold (maximize precision subject to recall ≥ 60%), and score the full customer base with both so the business can pick based on how expensive the intervention is.\n\n*Note on this run:* to validate the fix quickly, the Optuna trial counts below were reduced (25-40 trials per model instead of 50-200) for a fast confirmation pass on this container. The code itself is written with the original trial budgets so it should be re-run in Colab with full trial counts before finalizing; the ranking and recall gap are large enough that they are very unlikely to be an artifact of the smaller trial budget.","metadata":{}},{"id":"b7ffb747","cell_type":"code","source":"model_df=pd.read_csv('/kaggle/input/datasets/akshita2803/modeling/Modeling_Dataset.csv')","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-07-09T16:08:45.321454Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-07-09T16:08:45.321813Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-07-09T16:08:45.401250Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-07-09T16:08:45.321785Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-07-09T16:08:45.400558Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":2},{"id":"a076ffe2","cell_type":"code","source":"model_df.head()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-07-09T16:08:47.281235Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-07-09T16:08:47.281625Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-07-09T16:08:47.318424Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-07-09T16:08:47.281578Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-07-09T16:08:47.317578Z"}},"outputs":[{"execution_count":3,"output_type":"execute_result","data":{"text/plain":"   Loyalty Number  Male_Enc  Education_Enc  Marital_Enc  Card_Enc  \\\n0          480934         0              2            1         0   \n1          549612         1              1            2         0   \n2          429460         1              1            0         0   \n3  