}],"execution_count":56},{"id":"78cf5a4f-6e2f-4bce-a810-ab926935c265","cell_type":"markdown","source":"Local Explanation of a High-Risk Customer:\nFigure X presents the SHAP waterfall plot for a customer with a predicted churn probability of 95.3%. The explanation shows that the prediction is driven almost entirely by a complete absence of behavioral engagement. The customer recorded no flights, accumulated no loyalty points, traveled no distance, and remained inactive throughout the observation period. These behavioral signals collectively contribute to a very high predicted likelihood of churn. This demonstrates that the model bases its decisions on observable engagement patterns rather than demographic characteristics, allowing the airline to identify customers who have effectively disengaged before formal cancellation occurs.","metadata":{}},{"id":"700c5eeb-2288-4315-b5db-ee5a4dce7598","cell_type":"code","source":"explainer = shap.Explainer(final_model)\n\nshap_values = explainer(X_test)","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-07-09T17:28:32.711988Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-07-09T17:28:32.712408Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-07-09T17:28:33.048421Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-07-09T17:28:32.712379Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-07-09T17:28:33.047767Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":57},{"id":"0b0a7b58-33d4-436d-9447-d2f9ab295d33","cell_type":"code","source":"shap.plots.beeswarm( shap_values[:, :, 1])","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-07-09T17:28:33.950215Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-07-09T17:28:33.950646Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-07-09T17:28:34.529700Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-07-09T17:28:33.950617Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-07-09T17:28:34.528989Z"}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 800x550 with 2 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":58},{"id":"c4699736-fba5-4fb5-8df6-22929a85649d","cell_type":"markdown","source":"Key Insights\n\n* Flights_H1 is the most influential feature. Customers with low flight activity during the first half of the year (blue points) tend to have positive SHAP values, indicating a higher predicted probability of churn. In contrast, customers with frequent flights generally have negative SHAP values, reducing churn risk.\n* Total_Distance is another major predictor. Customers who have flown shorter cumulative distances contribute positively to churn predictions, whereas customers with higher travel distances are more likely to remain engaged.\n* Active_Months shows that customers who were active in fewer months are significantly more likely to churn. Consistent engagement throughout the year lowers the predicted churn probability.\n* Total_Flights, Flights_Q1, Flights_Q2, Avg_Flights_Month, and Max_Flights_Month all exhibit similar behavior.\n*  Lower flight frequency consistently increases churn risk, while higher flight activity has a protective effect.Total_Points_Acc also plays an important role. Customers earning fewer loyalty points are more likely to disengage from the loyalty program.\n","metadata":{}},{"id":"c35aef6c","cell_type":"code","source":"model_df.to_csv('Scored_Customers_v2.csv', index=False)\nprint(\"Scored dataset (v2, PR-AUC-selected model, dual threshold flags) exported.\")","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-07-09T17:21:16.284116Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-07-09T17:21:16.284903Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-07-09T17:21:16.496451Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-07-09T17:21:16.284866Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-07-09T17:21:16.495681Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Scored dataset (v2, PR-AUC-selected model, dual threshold flags) exported.\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":50},{"id":"3cef3a6b-1475-430f-ba38-d2bbedcb13ee","cell_type":"code","source":"","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null}]}
